        <!-- Marketplaces vs direct -->
        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Third-Party Marketplaces vs Direct Reservation Tools</h2>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Choosing between a marketplace and a direct reservation tool is a business model decision, not just a feature comparison. The choice affects buyer relationships, data ownership, and long-term program control.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Third-Party Marketplace Listings</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Third-party marketplaces are platforms where buyers discover breeders through the marketplace's audience. Examples include Good Dog, PuppyFind, and AKC Marketplace. The marketplace owns the buyer relationship and often charges fees or commissions.
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">
            <li class="flex items-start">
